Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Once hot, add the @ginger puree{15%g} and season with @salt{}. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and toast for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to a boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @teriyaki sauce{75%ml} and @sriracha sauce{30%ml}.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Using the back of a #spoon{}, brush enough teriyaki sauce over the salmon to coat all sides. Set aside the remaining sauce for later. Sprinkle over half of the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}.

Pop the radishes into a medium bowl with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar for pickling{1.5%tbsp}. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside to pickle.

In the meantime, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}. Trim the @pak choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the Tenderstem® and pak choi and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{}, then cover with a lid (or foil) and allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, pour in the @water for the sauce{50%ml} and the remaining teriyaki sriracha sauce and sesame seeds. Bring to the boil and simmer the sauce until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the salmon is cooked, gently peel off the skin.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through half of the spring onion and the pickling liquid from the radishes.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}, then spoon over the teriyaki sriracha sauce. Top with the garlicky veg, pickled radishes and glazed salmon fillet in separate sections.

Sprinkle the remaining spring onion over the top to finish. Enjoy!